WEBVTT

00:00.100 --> 00:02.025
[Vanessa] <i>Previously on
Penny Dreadful...</i>

00:02.027 --> 00:03.425
Your wife took her own life.

00:03.427 --> 00:05.194
That doesn't seem like her.

00:05.196 --> 00:06.629
It's like he doesn't care.

00:06.631 --> 00:08.964
[Sembene] <i>When he found
his son dead, I was there.</i>

00:08.966 --> 00:10.566
<i>This is not him.</i>

00:10.568 --> 00:13.068
- Maybe he just needs time.
- This... is not him.

00:13.070 --> 00:14.870
[Madame Kali] <i>I banished
the old bear to the cave</i>

00:14.872 --> 00:16.172
and lured out the cub.

00:16.174 --> 00:17.273
I feel like a new man.

00:17.275 --> 00:18.874
[Madame Kali]
<i>Only Miss Ives matters.</i>

00:18.876 --> 00:21.877
Time comes when the spider
must touch the fly.

00:21.879 --> 00:22.944
[Rusk] <i>"Whodunit?"</i>

00:22.946 --> 00:24.345
- [Ethan] <i>Inspector.</i>
- [Rusk] <i>Mr. Chandler.</i>

00:24.347 --> 00:25.814
[whispering]
I know you're involved.

00:25.816 --> 00:27.615
- And your proof?
- I'll find it.

00:27.617 --> 00:29.317
I always find it.

00:29.319 --> 00:31.019
I need to leave.
London isn't safe.

00:31.021 --> 00:31.987
I'll go with you.

00:33.089 --> 00:35.657
Enough. Whatever power
you held over me

00:35.659 --> 00:38.693
at the moment of
my bestial creation is gone.

00:38.695 --> 00:40.361
<i>I will see her.</i>

00:40.363 --> 00:42.363
She thinks you were her fiance
before the "accident"

00:42.365 --> 00:43.764
that robbed her of her memory.

00:43.766 --> 00:47.168
Let us start by being friends,
Mr. Clare. I can do no other.

00:47.170 --> 00:48.336
To my dear Angelique.

00:48.338 --> 00:50.838
And a special welcome
to Miss Frankenstein.

00:50.840 --> 00:52.173
Cheers.

00:52.175 --> 00:53.675
[Lily]
<i>My cousin is protective.</i>

00:53.752 --> 00:55.201
I don't think you need
much protection.

00:55.254 --> 00:57.871
<i>You are more capable
than you perhaps appear.</i>

00:57.923 --> 00:58.972
[Lily breathing heavily]

00:59.925 --> 01:01.074
[gasping]

01:03.000 --> 01:09.074
Learn the unknown English words
of this movie at www.skeebdo.com

01:11.353 --> 01:12.886
[Lily humming]

01:22.114 --> 01:23.463
[sighing]

01:25.651 --> 01:27.534
[chuckling]

01:29.621 --> 01:31.371
You're a very silly boy.

01:33.625 --> 01:35.408
That's what I like about you.

01:37.713 --> 01:41.131
Men should always
remain boys at heart.

01:41.166 --> 01:43.550
Filled with childish games,

01:45.087 --> 01:49.055
with Snakes and Ladders
and blindman's bluff.

01:51.476 --> 01:55.095
How sad that boys feel
they must grow up.

01:57.899 --> 02:00.183
[breathes deeply]

02:03.071 --> 02:05.105
You'll never grow up now.

02:19.521 --> 02:21.621
[humming]

02:29.131 --> 02:31.097
<i>♪</i>

03:51.561 --> 03:56.561
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

04:22.410 --> 04:23.576
[gasping]

04:24.996 --> 04:27.046
- [Mr. Clare] Where is she?
- What?

04:27.082 --> 04:28.581
Where is Lily?

04:28.633 --> 04:30.383
[continues gasping]

04:34.723 --> 04:36.389
- Where is she?
- [bucket clatters]

04:36.424 --> 04:38.091
[retching]

04:39.394 --> 04:40.593
She's not here?

04:47.352 --> 04:50.069
You let her go out
with a man by herself.

04:50.105 --> 04:52.539
- [grunts] What have you done?
- Stop it!

04:52.607 --> 04:54.607
Just stop! Give me a moment.

04:55.193 --> 04:58.778
[gasping]
She... Yes, she went out.

04:59.447 --> 05:02.248
She was meant
to come home and...

05:02.284 --> 05:03.533
[exclaiming]

05:03.585 --> 05:05.034
[breathing heavily]

05:06.788 --> 05:08.204
You made her for me.

05:10.041 --> 05:11.457
[Frankenstein whimpers]

05:12.043 --> 05:14.844
She is mine.
She is not yours.

05:15.847 --> 05:18.131
She is not his.
She is mine.

05:19.568 --> 05:21.067
I will take her!

05:22.687 --> 05:24.137
[Frankenstein grunts]

05:26.858 --> 05:29.809
And when we are gone,
far away from this place

05:30.512 --> 05:32.812
to a place
for she and me alone,

05:33.782 --> 05:36.716
I will return... Creator.

05:37.819 --> 05:40.153
I will return to you.

05:43.291 --> 05:44.657
One day...

05:45.243 --> 05:46.259
one night...

05:48.163 --> 05:51.331
I will show you the monster
you have made.

05:59.174 --> 06:01.808
[junior inspector]
Sir, you should see this.

06:03.011 --> 06:04.093
Inspector Galsworthy's

06:04.145 --> 06:05.845
appointment book
from last year.

06:05.847 --> 06:08.064
Note the listing
for September 27.

06:11.319 --> 06:13.236
Why would Sir Malcolm Murray
of all people

06:13.271 --> 06:14.520
visit Scotland Yard?

06:14.522 --> 06:15.688
That's what I thought,

06:15.740 --> 06:18.024
so I did a bit of digging
into the records.

06:24.532 --> 06:26.282
Seems I've a call to make.

06:29.671 --> 06:30.870
[Lyle]
I gave that up long ago.

06:33.675 --> 06:35.208
It was too embarrassing.

06:37.262 --> 06:40.463
Forever trying to remain fit
with rubdowns

06:41.683 --> 06:44.467
and medicine balls
and glandular injections,

06:46.221 --> 06:48.972
while always around me
there were more handsome men

06:49.024 --> 06:51.190
who had the thrill
of genuine youth.

06:53.728 --> 06:56.729
Guardsmen in shining uniforms

06:57.983 --> 07:00.566
and stable hands
with thick arms.

07:03.989 --> 07:05.038
Yes.

07:05.073 --> 07:06.155
[Madame Kali chuckles]

07:06.207 --> 07:08.825
I admit to vanity about
my complexion and hair color.

07:08.877 --> 07:11.244
What harm there, really?

07:11.296 --> 07:13.329
Do I render myself foolish?

07:13.381 --> 07:14.414
Well, hang a man for that

07:14.466 --> 07:16.382
and it'll be
a very crowded gallows.

07:19.504 --> 07:21.087
But then there's you.

07:22.974 --> 07:25.758
Quite a different paean
to youth we sing there.

07:26.678 --> 07:28.428
Well, we will sing it,
won't we?

07:28.480 --> 07:29.512
Oh, yes.

07:29.564 --> 07:32.649
The sword you dangle
over my head would cut deeply.

07:48.333 --> 07:50.283
You don't imagine you care
for those people?

07:51.619 --> 07:54.337
For Miss Ives and that
sorry lot at Grandage Place?

07:54.372 --> 07:56.506
I have long since given up
caring for anyone.

07:56.541 --> 07:57.957
Very sensible.

07:58.760 --> 08:00.460
Your future...

08:00.512 --> 08:03.463
rests entirely with me,
my dear friend.

08:04.182 --> 08:06.299
Whatever you desire,
the Master can give you.

08:06.301 --> 08:08.634
You don't need to tempt me,
I'm your creature.

08:12.774 --> 08:14.023
Where are Miss Ives
and Mr. Chandler?

08:14.059 --> 08:15.942
I don't know.
She wouldn't say.

08:17.779 --> 08:19.812
- When will they return?
- I've no idea.

08:20.815 --> 08:22.315
Does Mr. Chandler love her?

08:22.984 --> 08:23.950
Do you?

08:24.953 --> 08:26.202
[scoffs]

08:26.237 --> 08:28.821
- Does she love him?
- She's opaque.

08:29.491 --> 08:32.041
And you've absolutely no idea
where they've run off to?

08:32.077 --> 08:33.208
None.

08:35.246 --> 08:36.629
[gasps fearfully]

08:36.664 --> 08:39.332
- Are you telling me the truth?
- Yes.

08:39.384 --> 08:41.417
I can feel your blood pumping.

08:41.469 --> 08:44.754
The most minute pressure
and the artery is open to me.

08:44.806 --> 08:47.673
Your blood would paint
this room.

08:47.675 --> 08:49.225
[shuddering]

08:51.046 --> 08:52.011
Ah.

08:53.815 --> 08:55.398
I know you're not lying.

08:56.684 --> 08:58.434
You always bat your eyelashes
most coquettishly

08:58.486 --> 08:59.852
when you lie.
[chuckles]

09:01.106 --> 09:02.855
Ah, well, then, [sighs]

09:02.857 --> 09:05.024
if Miss Ives
has gone to ground,

09:05.076 --> 09:07.326
I shall have to lure her back.

09:10.081 --> 09:11.330
Kiss me and go.

09:12.584 --> 09:14.033
I'm bored with you.

09:18.289 --> 09:19.372
No.

09:27.799 --> 09:29.215
[Lyle gasps]

09:39.227 --> 09:41.527
You taste like
a fat little man.

09:57.245 --> 09:58.628
[breathing shakily]

10:19.801 --> 10:21.834
- [Lyle yelps]
- What did she say?

10:23.905 --> 10:26.606
Ask her yourself.

10:26.658 --> 10:29.158
I am not so sentimental
as my mother.

10:30.445 --> 10:32.445
Where is the future, Mr. Lyle?

10:33.081 --> 10:35.114
With her age or my youth?

10:36.618 --> 10:38.918
Whatever she promises you
is a lie.

10:38.953 --> 10:41.621
Whatever I promise you
is a lie

10:41.673 --> 10:43.623
but you'll live longer
with me.

10:45.877 --> 10:48.794
Now... tell me
about Mr. Chandler.

10:57.305 --> 11:04.586
[young Mina]
<i>Did you catch one?</i>

11:04.621 --> 11:06.171
[young Peter]
<i>In Africa? Really?</i>

11:07.190 --> 11:09.341
- [knocking at door]
- Come in.

11:14.431 --> 11:16.798
There's a gentleman here
for you...

11:16.850 --> 11:18.466
from Scotland Yard.

11:27.377 --> 11:28.727
How do you do, Sir Malcolm?

11:28.779 --> 11:30.862
My name is
Inspector Bartholomew Rusk,

11:30.897 --> 11:32.147
Scotland Yard.

11:34.785 --> 11:36.785
Inspector, to what
do I owe the pleasure?

11:36.820 --> 11:39.537
You have a martial sense
in decoration, Sir Malcolm.

11:39.573 --> 11:41.322
Apparently, I do.

11:41.324 --> 11:42.657
Please, take a seat.

11:43.243 --> 11:44.626
What can I do for you,
Inspector?

11:44.661 --> 11:46.578
Are you interested
in criminology?

11:46.630 --> 11:49.164
What? No. Not especially.

11:49.216 --> 11:50.248
- No?
- No.

11:51.084 --> 11:53.168
[Rusk] I didn't mean it
as an insinuation of any sort.

11:53.587 --> 11:57.088
Many people are intrigued by
the morbid events in our city.

11:57.674 --> 11:59.257
Why are you here, Inspector?

11:59.309 --> 12:02.010
I should like to know why
you visited Scotland Yard

12:02.012 --> 12:04.145
on September the 27th
last year

12:04.181 --> 12:06.598
to speak with
my predecessor...

12:06.650 --> 12:08.433
Inspector Galsworthy.

12:09.186 --> 12:10.819
Oh, yes, that.

12:12.189 --> 12:14.355
Rather whimsical
sort of thing actually.

12:16.526 --> 12:19.577
- What did you talk about?
- I barely remember.

12:19.663 --> 12:21.496
I spoke to him an hour ago.

12:21.531 --> 12:23.915
You asked him about
the Spitalfields murders.

12:25.102 --> 12:27.202
You were quite insistent
that he...

12:27.287 --> 12:29.838
"Stop hunting for a man

12:30.791 --> 12:32.674
and start hunting
for a beast."

12:39.282 --> 12:40.482
Why would you say that?

12:42.085 --> 12:43.184
I don't recall.

12:45.522 --> 12:48.773
The whole thing was, um...
[clears throat] a caprice.

12:48.809 --> 12:50.558
- A caprice?
- Something like that.

12:50.560 --> 12:52.110
You don't seem...

12:53.530 --> 12:55.230
- a capricious man.
- Don't I?

12:56.283 --> 12:58.366
You have a tripod of rifles
at your window.

12:58.401 --> 13:00.869
Well, can't I decorate
my own house as I see fit?

13:01.872 --> 13:03.288
Any way you like.

13:04.908 --> 13:06.958
- Do you live here alone?
- What?

13:08.962 --> 13:10.829
No. I have...

13:12.249 --> 13:13.915
a ward and my man Sembene.

13:13.917 --> 13:15.834
- Other servants?
- No.

13:15.886 --> 13:17.252
In a house this large?

13:18.088 --> 13:19.137
We make do.

13:19.973 --> 13:21.589
You have a front door
made of steel.

13:22.425 --> 13:24.225
There have been robberies
in the neighborhood.

13:24.261 --> 13:25.593
Oh, I'm so sorry.

13:26.997 --> 13:28.897
That door could
keep out a beast,

13:28.932 --> 13:29.931
wouldn't you say?

13:29.983 --> 13:32.724
Inspector Rusk,
I'm not to be trifled with.

13:32.759 --> 13:36.152
You filed a missing persons report
on June 12th last year.

13:37.095 --> 13:38.565
Your daughter, Mina.

13:39.918 --> 13:40.496
Yes.

13:40.531 --> 13:43.659
You visited Scotland Yard
7 times in the next 6 weeks.

13:44.019 --> 13:46.419
- And then you stopped coming.
- Yes.

13:47.956 --> 13:49.756
Might I ask why?

13:52.344 --> 13:53.426
My daughter's deceased.

13:53.479 --> 13:55.095
I know.
I have the burial records

13:55.147 --> 13:57.848
from Margate,
dated January the 4th.

13:58.600 --> 14:00.100
But there was
no death certificate filed

14:00.152 --> 14:01.601
with the Magistrate.

14:01.603 --> 14:02.769
It was a private affair.

14:02.805 --> 14:06.573
There are no private burials
in this country, sir.

14:06.608 --> 14:07.674
Title or not.

14:07.709 --> 14:09.242
The circumstances of her death

14:09.278 --> 14:10.527
were embarrassing
to my family,

14:10.579 --> 14:12.879
I used my influence
to ensure discretion.

14:14.833 --> 14:16.149
That is illegal.

14:17.452 --> 14:19.085
She was my daughter.

14:19.121 --> 14:20.587
Well, many people have
daughters and obey the law.

14:20.622 --> 14:22.122
Well, I didn't!

14:35.838 --> 14:36.970
You know him.

14:39.241 --> 14:40.874
- No.
- Look closely.

14:41.710 --> 14:44.227
American.
6'3", I would say.

14:44.897 --> 14:46.196
Means nothing.

14:46.899 --> 14:48.031
Is he a suspect?

14:48.066 --> 14:49.950
You're sure
you don't recognize him?

14:49.985 --> 14:51.318
Entirely sure.

14:52.988 --> 14:54.287
Are you confident
in that answer?

14:54.323 --> 14:55.789
Would you like
to summon a lawyer

14:55.824 --> 14:56.907
and take a deposition?

14:56.959 --> 14:58.158
In time.

15:00.629 --> 15:02.295
Should you come
across anything

15:02.331 --> 15:03.697
that would aid
in our investigation,

15:03.732 --> 15:05.966
don't hesitate
to stop by Scotland Yard.

15:07.836 --> 15:09.052
You know the way.

15:11.940 --> 15:13.807
Good day, Sir Malcolm.

15:28.919 --> 15:30.769
- [door slams]
- [Lily] Victor!

15:30.821 --> 15:32.154
[breathing heavily]

15:36.694 --> 15:38.860
- Where have you been?
- I'm so sorry.

15:39.697 --> 15:40.996
I know you must
have been worried.

15:41.031 --> 15:42.614
You'll hardly believe it.

15:43.283 --> 15:46.118
- What happened to my curtains?
- Lily, where have you been?

15:47.621 --> 15:49.671
First, kiss me good morning

15:49.707 --> 15:52.257
like my true friend
and calm yourself.

15:54.344 --> 15:55.594
[chuckles]

15:58.298 --> 16:03.685
I had a most entertaining
evening with Mr. Gray.

16:03.721 --> 16:05.103
We went to a waxworks.

16:05.139 --> 16:06.938
Have you ever been
to one of those?

16:07.691 --> 16:10.142
- Yes.
- Well, after that...

16:11.361 --> 16:13.228
I just felt like taking a walk

16:13.280 --> 16:14.696
and I completely
lost track of time.

16:14.732 --> 16:19.067
Finally, I got so tired that
I sat on a bench in Hyde Park

16:19.153 --> 16:21.620
to rest my feet and... [sighs]

16:21.655 --> 16:23.438
next thing I knew
it was morning.

16:24.374 --> 16:26.742
I could have been murdered
in my sleep.

16:30.798 --> 16:32.714
Did you get me flowers?

16:33.300 --> 16:36.334
Victor, you are such
a good friend.

16:37.221 --> 16:38.720
They're not from me.

16:39.890 --> 16:41.056
[chuckles]

16:41.759 --> 16:42.924
From Mr. Gray, I take it?

16:43.894 --> 16:45.727
What a strange
sort of man he is.

16:45.763 --> 16:47.229
Isn't he though?

16:47.264 --> 16:48.897
He's awfully charming...

16:49.817 --> 16:52.901
but I think a little
too sophisticated for me.

16:52.936 --> 16:54.069
Lily.

16:54.938 --> 16:58.190
We should think about
getting away.

16:58.242 --> 17:01.359
- Away where?
- I don't know.

17:02.613 --> 17:04.112
Leave London.

17:05.332 --> 17:07.616
- Take a bit of a holiday.
- Nonsense.

17:08.752 --> 17:09.951
I'm just getting
used to the place,

17:10.002 --> 17:12.454
and you have so much more
to teach me, don't you?

17:17.845 --> 17:20.962
I'm safe... here with you.

17:21.598 --> 17:23.265
This is our home.

17:26.637 --> 17:27.803
Now...

17:29.356 --> 17:32.357
if I know my boy, he hasn't
thought about breakfast.

17:33.811 --> 17:34.860
[exhales sharply]

17:34.895 --> 17:36.895
I'll make your favorite
poached eggs.

17:38.949 --> 17:40.565
'Cause you're so good.

17:42.152 --> 17:43.118
[chuckles]

17:50.544 --> 17:52.994
Wait.
Don't bother about breakfast.

17:54.665 --> 17:55.714
I'm going out.

17:57.167 --> 17:58.466
[Lily] All right.

17:59.136 --> 18:01.469
Can you bring back
some butter and eggs?

18:01.505 --> 18:03.138
We're running low.

18:07.144 --> 18:08.176
Yes.

18:17.855 --> 18:20.188
<i>It was the veins in my arms
that told me.</i>

18:21.525 --> 18:23.942
When they collapse,
you have to find fresh ones.

18:24.695 --> 18:26.561
I'm running short.

18:27.581 --> 18:29.414
So I'm addicted.

18:29.449 --> 18:31.283
Which is no great terror
to me...

18:32.703 --> 18:34.586
but the cause...

18:36.123 --> 18:37.289
Pain.

18:39.293 --> 18:44.045
I don't have the proper tools
to perform this operation.

18:44.047 --> 18:45.680
I don't know what
I'm doing...

18:46.416 --> 18:47.682
honestly.

18:48.952 --> 18:51.286
Oh, we're all neophytes
in love, Victor.

18:52.089 --> 18:53.388
None of us have the tools,

18:53.423 --> 18:55.757
or the weapons,
or the resources.

18:55.792 --> 18:59.594
Prepared as we think we are,
we're defeated.

18:59.630 --> 19:03.315
[scoffs]
I have surmounted in my life.

19:05.202 --> 19:08.286
It's been my inexorable
pattern of behavior.

19:09.406 --> 19:11.139
No mystery too deep...

19:11.808 --> 19:13.408
no puzzle too complex.

19:16.046 --> 19:18.046
They've fallen before me.

19:21.168 --> 19:23.752
I don't know what wisdom
I can offer.

19:25.839 --> 19:28.890
We're in the same
unknown jungle, my friend.

19:28.926 --> 19:31.426
We have to thrash
our way out alone.

19:31.478 --> 19:33.428
Isn't that what love is?

19:34.398 --> 19:36.898
And if we're in danger of
losing that love, and that...

19:37.851 --> 19:40.936
creates greater panic still,
what do we do then?

19:42.439 --> 19:44.339
We suffer in our own ways.

19:45.876 --> 19:48.443
But we're all unequal
to the task.

19:49.546 --> 19:50.779
We are...

19:52.883 --> 19:54.215
enchanted.

19:59.506 --> 20:00.789
All my life, I've been a man

20:00.841 --> 20:02.791
who sought
singular achievement

20:02.843 --> 20:05.427
and fed on rage
and dissatisfaction.

20:07.047 --> 20:09.881
My character was one of
monomaniacal anger.

20:11.268 --> 20:13.518
My blood thrilled to the lash.

20:16.139 --> 20:19.140
I was cruel to my wife,
and to my children,

20:19.142 --> 20:21.860
and grew more famous
in the process...

20:23.230 --> 20:24.312
more myself.

20:26.483 --> 20:27.532
And now?

20:27.567 --> 20:29.317
I've become alienated
from the cruel man

20:29.369 --> 20:31.703
who used to look back at me
in the mirror.

20:36.827 --> 20:38.493
What is this face, Doctor?

20:40.247 --> 20:43.164
Is it the one you knew,
and properly feared?

20:44.634 --> 20:47.168
I've... seen you grow content.

20:47.170 --> 20:49.504
You've seen me grow
into a happy man.

20:50.841 --> 20:52.257
But look deeper.

20:54.311 --> 20:55.810
That's not who I am.

20:57.814 --> 21:00.648
