without Victor.

39:30.259 --> 39:32.459
Perhaps you should
come back another time.

39:35.848 --> 39:37.381
Why are you so quiet?

39:38.801 --> 39:41.135
You're never usually
at a loss for words.

39:41.554 --> 39:44.354
Aren't there some verses
you could recite?

39:47.026 --> 39:48.892
Stop pretending
you're frightened.

39:49.812 --> 39:50.944
[voice shuddering]
Please leave.

39:53.149 --> 39:54.565
Who are you?

39:55.034 --> 39:57.201
What... What do you mean?

39:57.953 --> 39:59.903
Who are you?

39:59.955 --> 40:01.488
Honestly, I think
you're more able

40:01.490 --> 40:03.991
to answer
that question than I.

40:03.993 --> 40:06.827
My past is unknown to me,
as well you know.

40:06.879 --> 40:07.995
Is it?

40:09.798 --> 40:11.465
[Lily]
What are you talking about?

40:13.502 --> 40:15.586
[Mr. Clare]
Did you enjoy your evening?

40:16.055 --> 40:17.137
What?

40:17.923 --> 40:19.306
With that young man.

40:20.226 --> 40:21.842
Were you spying on me?

40:21.844 --> 40:23.594
Did you enjoy your evening?

40:23.679 --> 40:26.930
Yes, I did. Now, please leave.

40:26.982 --> 40:28.849
This behavior is
really insupportable!

40:28.901 --> 40:31.018
- When Victor hears of this...
- There is no Victor!

40:31.053 --> 40:32.603
- [Lily gasps]
- There is no young man!

40:32.655 --> 40:34.988
- There is thee and me!
- All right! Very well!

40:35.024 --> 40:37.524
What in God's name
do you want of me?

40:37.576 --> 40:40.827
What I want I cannot have.
You're incapable of it.

40:40.863 --> 40:42.913
Yes, I know.

40:45.668 --> 40:48.068
You want to walk
in the village

40:48.103 --> 40:50.337
and hold my hand.

40:50.372 --> 40:51.605
And when people are cruel,

40:51.640 --> 40:54.041
you want me to love you
even more.

40:55.911 --> 40:57.144
Do I hurt you?

40:58.280 --> 40:59.413
[Lily scoffs]

40:59.815 --> 41:01.682
You pathetic creature.

41:02.818 --> 41:06.153
How can you imagine
that I could care for you?

41:07.223 --> 41:10.774
Does that face
belong alongside this?

41:12.978 --> 41:15.229
Doesn't the world smile on us?

41:16.198 --> 41:18.315
Don't we make
a beautiful couple,

41:18.367 --> 41:19.783
"thee and me"?

41:19.818 --> 41:22.152
Shall we wander the pastures
and recite

41:22.204 --> 41:24.738
your fucking poetry
to the fucking cows?

41:24.790 --> 41:26.573
You are blind...

41:27.543 --> 41:29.243
like all other men.

41:29.295 --> 41:30.911
And you are unlike
all other women.

41:31.630 --> 41:33.080
[both grunt]

41:34.633 --> 41:36.049
You tell me how.

41:38.921 --> 41:41.722
We flatter our men
with our pain.

41:42.675 --> 41:44.758
We bow before them.

41:44.760 --> 41:48.312
We make ourselves dolls
for their amusement.

41:48.347 --> 41:52.182
We lose our dignity in corsets
and high shoes

41:52.234 --> 41:54.818
and gossip
and the slavery of marriage!

41:54.853 --> 41:56.436
And our reward
for this service?

41:57.690 --> 41:59.072
[voice breaking]
The back of the hand...

42:01.076 --> 42:03.694
the face
turned to the pillow...

42:03.746 --> 42:05.946
the bloody, aching cunt

42:05.998 --> 42:08.081
as you force us onto your beds

42:08.117 --> 42:09.783
to take your
fat, heaving bodies!

42:09.818 --> 42:11.251
[crying]

42:11.287 --> 42:13.503
You drag us into the alleys,
my lad,

42:13.539 --> 42:16.173
and cram yourselves
into our mouths for two bob

42:16.759 --> 42:19.126
when you're
not beating us senseless!

42:19.178 --> 42:21.428
When we're not bloody
from the eyes,

42:21.463 --> 42:23.797
and the mouth, and the ass
and the cunt!

42:23.849 --> 42:24.798
[Mr. Clare grunting]

42:26.018 --> 42:27.517
[both panting]

42:33.442 --> 42:34.641
Never again...

42:37.363 --> 42:40.981
will I kneel to any man.

42:44.236 --> 42:46.370
Now they shall kneel to me.

42:49.074 --> 42:50.791
As you do, monster.

42:50.826 --> 42:52.159
[trembling]

42:56.332 --> 42:57.831
My monster.

43:00.419 --> 43:02.636
My beautiful corpse.

43:08.227 --> 43:11.178
How clever he's been,
our creator.

43:14.149 --> 43:15.565
But our little god...

43:16.602 --> 43:18.852
has brought forth
not angels...

43:20.406 --> 43:21.738
but demons.

43:23.025 --> 43:24.825
Thee and me.

43:28.530 --> 43:31.531
And what should we do
with this power, undead thing?

43:33.285 --> 43:35.869
You're a thoughtful man,
a philosopher even.

43:35.921 --> 43:39.172
So tell me, why do we exist?

43:41.260 --> 43:43.710
Why have we been chosen?
Tell me.

43:46.932 --> 43:48.048
I don't know.

43:50.302 --> 43:51.885
Is it to suffer?

43:54.723 --> 43:55.722
Yes.

44:00.062 --> 44:01.278
Must it be?

44:02.598 --> 44:04.131
How can it be other?

44:05.934 --> 44:07.567
We long
for that we cannot have.

44:08.103 --> 44:09.236
Women?

44:10.105 --> 44:12.406
I'll bring you a dozen.
We'll fuck 'em together.

44:16.145 --> 44:17.210
Me?

44:21.417 --> 44:23.300
Then you shall have me.

44:26.171 --> 44:27.587
I want you.

44:29.057 --> 44:30.323
[Mr. Clare shuddering]

44:31.760 --> 44:36.062
I want a man
unlike all other men.

44:36.648 --> 44:37.681
My brother,

44:38.767 --> 44:40.233
my equal.

44:42.020 --> 44:43.236
I'll take you...

44:45.107 --> 44:46.606
by this beautiful,

44:47.276 --> 44:52.028
